body:
This looks better. One more thing to think about - what about a spec that says:

<pre>
subject { {:a => 'b'} }
its(:keys) { should eq([:a]) }
</pre>

dchelimsky: I would wonder if that scenario though goes against what its(:method_name) is usually comparing. I think if its a long key array, the tests would be better served as doing

```
its(:keys) { should include?(:a) }
its(:keys) { should include?(:b) }
```

but then your repeating yourself. Otherwise if the test fails you have to debug which key is in there and which isnt from the result message.
